  "content": [
    {
      "id": "block_1",
      "type": "text",
      "latex": "Pour tout $k \\in \\N$, on pose \n$$X_k = \\left(\\frac{2}{1+k} , 1+e^{-k} \\right) \\in \\R^2$$",
      "html": "<p>Pour tout <span>\\(k \\in \\N\\)</span>, on pose\n<span>\\[X_k = \\left(\\frac{2}{1+k} , 1+e^{-k} \\right) \\in \\R^2\\]</span></p>",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "block_2",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Soit $\\ell = (0,1)$. Calculer $||X_k-\\ell||_{2}$ où $||.||_{2}$ est la norme euclidienne.",
      "html": "<p>Soit <span>\\(\\ell = (0,1)\\)</span>. Calculer <span>\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2}\\)</span> où <span>\\(||.||_{2}\\)</span> est la norme euclidienne.</p>",
      "order": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "block_3",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "$||X_k-\\ell||_{2} = \\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{2}{1+k}\\right)^2 + \\left(e^{-k}\\right)^2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{(1+k)^2} + e^{-2k} }$",
      "html": "<p><span>\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2} = \\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{2}{1+k}\\right)^2 + \\left(e^{-k}\\right)^2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{(1+k)^2} + e^{-2k} }\\)</span></p>",
      "order": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "block_4",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "En déduire la convergence de la suite $(X_k)$ dans $\\R^2$.",
      "html": "<p>En déduire la convergence de la suite <span>\\((X_k)\\)</span> dans <span>\\(\\R^2\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "block_5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "$||X_k-\\ell||_{2} \\xrightarrow[k \\to +\\infty]{}0$ donc $X_k \\xrightarrow[k \\to +\\infty]{}\\ell$.",
      "html": "<p><span>\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2} \\xrightarrow[k \\to +\\infty]{}0\\)</span> donc <span>\\(X_k \\xrightarrow[k \\to +\\infty]{}\\ell\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 5
    }
  ],
